# Terminal Commands Used
## Server Side:

- cd server: Navigates into the server directory.
- npm init -y: Initializes a Node.js application with default settings.
- npm install express mongoose cors nodemon: Installs the necessary backend dependencies,.
- node index.js: Runs the server manually.
- npm start: Runs the server using nodemon (after configuring the script in package.json) to automatically restart on file changes.

## Client Side:
- npx create-react-app: Generates the boilerplate React application.
- cd client: Navigates into the client directory.
- npm install axios: Installs the library used for making API requests.
- npm start: Launches the React development server locally on port 3000.